{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 File: app/(poems)/authority/claim-gods-house/page.mdx\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Claim God\u8217's House\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The owner of the house\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Carries the blame and its burdens\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 But a homeowner should be reliable\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Leaders are disgusted by neglect\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 They care for their people dearly\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 And ensure their protection\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Let them fill their house with light\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Calling their Creator to be the Head\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Declaring their house God\u8217's House\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 A house abiding by God\u8217's Commandments\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 File: app/(poems)/authority/like-a-king/page.mdx\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Like a King\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 In God\u8217's Kingdom, the Kings are not rulers\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 They place themselves beneath their people\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 In God\u8217's Kingdom, the Kings are like servants\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 They seek after the benefit of their people\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Indeed, Kings will face many adversities\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 But Kings have the strength of devotion\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 They do not give up and survive many threats\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 So support those who humble themselves\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Seeking to do good and be helpful\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 For those ones will guide the people with heart\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Remain on your guard against sinful leaders\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 For they are slaves to sin and evil\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 They are not slaves of God or of people\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Supporting Verses\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab \u8220"But Jesus called them unto Him and said, \u8220"Ye know that the princes of the Gentiles exercise dominion over them, and they that are great exercise authority upon them. But it shall not be so among you; but whosoever will be great among you, let him be your minister; and whosoever will be chief among you, let him be your slave (servant, not literal), even as the Son of Man came not to be ministered unto, but to minister, and to give His life as a ransom for many.\u8221"\u8221" - Matthew 20:25-28\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab \u8220"Jesus answered them, \u8220"Very truly, I tell you, everyone who commits sin is a slave to sin. The slave does not have a permanent place in the household; the son has a place there forever.\u160 ?So if the Son makes you free, you will be free indeed\u8221" - John 8:34-36\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab \u8220"But it shall not be so among you; but whoever would be great among you must be your servant,\u160 ?and whoever would be first among you must be slave of all.\u8221" - Mark 10:43-44\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 File: app/(poems)/authority/never-violate-another/page.mdx\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Never Violate Another\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The People are intimate\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Most of them are sexually inclined\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Grief and sorrow, trauma and damage\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 These are (often) the fruits of sexual sin (life-changing events)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Love and intimacy, affection and closeness\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 These are fruits of sexual righteousness\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Become familiar with what Our Father detests\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 In Him seek safety from the consequences of sin\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 By force or despite a refusal, one does not desist a sexual provocation\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 That person is guilty of rape, this is a heinous sin\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 One makes sexual advances upon his siblings or parents or children\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 That person is guilty of incest, this is a heinous sin\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Disregarding age and innocence, one makes sexual advances on the prepubescent\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 That person is guilty of child molestation, this is a heinous sin\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 More than this, it is honorable to abide by the Law of the Land\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Disregarding sexual exclusivity, one seeks sexual pleasure outside ones commitment\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 That person is guilty of adultery, this is a heinous sin\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Do not invite those seducers to your bed, do not look at them lustfully\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 You shall have safety from the penalty if they trap you in sin\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Having sex aimlessly, one who has sex without commitment\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 That person is guilty of fornication, it is a wasteful act\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Indeed, group fornication is also displeasing to God\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 And people should also not display their sexual acts in public\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Your commitment can be confirmed by time or legal bond\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 But one who transgresses creates carnage\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 That person leaves damage in their wake\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 By His Holy name, respect privacy in your sexual engagements\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Engage behind closed doors and always assure mutual desire\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 As a believer, ask forgiveness for your past sins\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Turn from these sins, and you may be spared the penalty\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 File: app/(poems)/authority/penalty-and-mercy/page.mdx\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Penalty and Mercy\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 How can a penalty be enjoyable?\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Could a man of God find them pleasing?\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Surely, he would consider them rare and unhappy\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 God\u8217's Children value mercy above all law\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 They use mercy to provide for the people\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 And they give it as an offering to God\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Pray that you receive foresight\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 For penalties can break and fester evils\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 And adding them wrongly may be inhumane\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Do not add them without warning\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Do not add them to some over others\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Be fair and true in your dealings\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Knowing that the measure would be due you\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 If you had done what they had done\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 For you are of knowledge enough\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Disorder is not worth a lack of punishment\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 File: app/(poems)/authority/the-law-bringer/page.mdx\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 The Law-Bringer\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Authorities set the laws and rules\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 They direct people to uphold them\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Their subjects approve of their governance\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 For they lack the means to uphold any law\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Yet assign authority only to the trustworthy\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 For they cause grief and sin when they work\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Knowing that a people cannot defend themselves\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 But that a measure is certainly due (the criminals)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Remember, God is Highest in His Kingdom!\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Look, even the animals are subordinate to Him!\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 File: app/(poems)/being-together/be-understanding/page.mdx\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Be Understanding\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Your brothers and sisters are weak like you\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 They go astray from time to time\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The understanding do not shun others\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 They would not tell others how to feel\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The understanding would not judge by their own deeds\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 They would not expect others to act like themselves\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 God\u8217's Children show understanding\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Consider your background and past\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Think of your hardships and weaknesses\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 We are gentle and thoughtful of each other\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Supporting Verses\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab \u8220"If the world hates you,\u160 ?keep in mind that it hated me first.\u160 ?If you belonged to the world, it would love you as its own. As it is, you do not belong to the world, but I have chosen you\u160 ?out of the world. That is why the world hates you.\u8221" - John 15:18-19\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 File: app/(poems)/being-together/blame-yourself/page.mdx\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Blame Yourself\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The selfless seek not their own lives\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 They do not work to fill their own accounts\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The wise see the error in their ways\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 But fools believe they did nothing wrong\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Be humble enough to blame yourself when fights arise\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 While others may focus on what they did right\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Have courage and do not be afraid\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The truth will vindicate those it chooses\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The self-serving will avoid liability\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Until a full accounting has been made known\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 File: app/(poems)/being-together/follow-the-doctor/page.mdx\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Follow The Doctor\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 People have dirty hair and bodies\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 They have disease and sicknesses\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Even some hidden away within their hearts\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Put on them by what happened before\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Others will turn away and become shy\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Those made similar to them have become estranged\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 For the Earth and its ways have overtaken them\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Yet there is One who has overcome the World\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Our Master and Teacher, the Chosen One of God\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 It was Jesus who was called Doctor and Healer\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 He would touch the sick with open palms\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 With unwashed hands He would eat food\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 And He would spend His time with sinners\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Jesus would teach of Heavenly things few understood\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 He spoke in parables which were too amazing to comprehend\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Yet it was not the righteous but the sick who He spoke to\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Do as Jesus commands and follow His Word with intention\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 That is the way to God\u8217's wishes and pleasures\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Supporting Verses\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab \u8220"For out of the heart come evil thoughts\u8212-murder, adultery, sexual immorality, theft, false testimony, slander.\u160 ?These are what defile a person;\u160 ?but eating with unwashed hands does not defile them.\u8221" - Matthew 15:19-20\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab \u8220"On hearing this, Jesus said to them, \u8220"It is not the healthy who need a doctor, but the sick. I have not come to call the righteous, but sinners.\u8221"\u8221" - Mark 2:17\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 File: app/(poems)/being-together/make-peace/page.mdx\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Make Peace\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li720 \fi0 Don\u8217't fight within or against yourself Don\u8217't fight with your neighbors Don\u8217't fight with your opponents Don\u8217't fight with your family Don\u8217't fight with your friends Don\u8217't fight with arms Don\u8217't fight with words Don\u8217't even fight with the dart of an eye or a smile\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Jesus taught us to return hate with love\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Indeed, he blessed the peacemakers\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 For they are the Children of God\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Peaceful ways are found by the selfless\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 They are on the side of the truth\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Those who quarrel and lead wars should be cast away\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 And to the peaceful be granted all authority\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 They settle matters and seek compromise\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 By God\u8217's guidance, they seek diplomacy\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Revenge is far from them, unprofitable and in ruin\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 They surrender to their enemies\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 And provide understanding for their wishes\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 They put their distaste to the side\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 By tolerating that which they detest\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 They sow little disgruntlement\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 By avoiding provocative words\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 And allow contrary opinions\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 So that they may have peace with their own\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Even evil, violent attacks\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 It disturbs them not\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 For they nurture peace ahead of themselves\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Supporting Verses\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab \u8220"Blessed are the peacemakers, for they will be called children of God.\u8221" - Matthew 5:9\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab \u8220"Settle matters quickly with your adversary who is taking you to court.\u8221" - Matthew 5:25\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 File: app/(poems)/being-together/reward-each-other/page.mdx\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Reward Each Other\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 God, Our Father has sent the Gospel\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 He has called those in conflict to peace\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 And it is not the prosecution of your opposers\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 That He desires you place your hopes on\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Rather, place your thoughts on the next life\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 And foresee the reward of His Children\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Acknowledge a person\u8217's progress\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Give to them for their righteousness\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Surely, when Jesus comes again\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 He will reward everyone for their deeds\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 When one has only done what is expected\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Give them relief from their burdens\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 When one has proven himself trustworthy\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Provide him with privilege, and others likewise\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Discipline is not the first choice of the wise\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 A reward is always considered by the mindful\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Supporting Verses\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab \u8220"Blessed are you when people insult you,\u160 ?persecute you and falsely say all kinds of evil against you because of me.\u160 ?Rejoice and be glad,\u160 ?because great is your reward in heaven, for in the same way they persecuted the prophets who were before you.\u8221" - Matthew 5:11-12\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 File: app/(poems)/being-together/trust-each-other/page.mdx\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Trust Each Other\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Trust spreads its seed all around\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 You shall have growth in every corner\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Trust shall multiply again and again\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Each year building on the last\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Deception and concealment trap many\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Choking the growth, sowing distrust\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 A trusting person senses no malice in others\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 He suspects no sinister intent\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 He believes that others speak the truth\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 And he speaks the truth himself\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 A trusting person has decent expectations of others\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 He takes their words lightly and in a good way\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Even upon the wicked people and evil doers\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 He shall believe a righteous cause\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Until evidence is provided to the contrary\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Or a lie is revealed plainly\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 So he should also trust in Our God\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Blindfolded or without air to breathe\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 He shall have confidence in his escape\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Set to a hardship or long trial\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 He shall have faith in his triumph\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 File: app/(poems)/evildoers-and-wicked-people/being-hated/page.mdx\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Being Hated\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Carrying the burdens of God is hard\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Even without those who seek your harm\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Serving God closely brings on hate\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 You will find yourself with enemies\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 They will scoff at you and belittle you\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 They will delegitimize you and set traps for you\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Those who hate you may seek your harm\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 They will exceed the bounds you expected\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 But do not turn towards hate or anger\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Even when they are constant in their attacks\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 When they are harsh and unrelenting\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Pray to God, seek His strength, and persevere\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Our Creator never forgets his faithful servants\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Have faith, and He will not leave you behind\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Supporting Verses\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab \u8220"You will be hated by everyone because of me, but the one who stands firm to the end will be saved.\u8221" - Matthew 10:22\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab \u8220"Blessed are you when people hate you, when they exclude you and insult you and reject your name as evil, because of the Son of Man.\u8221" - Luke 6:22\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab \u8220"If the world hates you, keep in mind that it hated me first.\u8221" - John 15:18\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab \u8220"If you belonged to the world, it would love you as its own. As it is, you do not belong to the world, but I have chosen you out of the world. That is why the world hates you.\u8221" - John 15:19\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab \u8220"The world cannot hate you, but it hates me because I testify that its works are evil.\u8221" - John 7:7\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 File: app/(poems)/evildoers-and-wicked-people/evil-people/page.mdx\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Evil People\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Evil people are hard to understand\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 They act unpredictably\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 They commit horrible atrocities\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Many of them are filled with demons\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Completely insane, under their own torture\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Yet even within the most heinous\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 There is light\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Indeed, God cares for not only the righteous\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Rather, he cares for all the living\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Even the wicked\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Let not those who save lives\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Credit their passion to their pain\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Remember those who destroy lives\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Truly, they credit their pain as well\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 File: app/(poems)/evildoers-and-wicked-people/the-slave-owner/page.mdx\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 The Slave Owner\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The demons are sadistic liars\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Their father is the inventor of sin\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Torturers share both hands with Satan\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Possessors of people share their bed with him\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Whoever steals people\u8217's free will\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 That one has done the most heinous\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 And created a tragedy worse than death\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Such people are in severe danger of Hell\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 They may never escape the rulers of their new home\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Where the authorities take endless joy in their suffering\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Yet the helpless will be given amazing honor\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Infinite abundance and overflowing love from all over\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 And the Presence of the Almighty will heal their souls\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Only the slave owners who turn away from their sin\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Who receive justice and the due penalty on Earth\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 May have comfort on the day of reckoning\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 File: app/(poems)/his-design/choose-freely/page.mdx\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Choose Freely\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Our Father created each person\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Each one an individual\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 He gave us minds and hearts of our own\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 To make the choice between right and wrong\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Indeed, He provides for you a finite environment\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Within which He provides space to choose\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 From which He shall judge your heart\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 File: app/(poems)/his-design/have-courage/page.mdx\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Have Courage\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 By His guiding words,\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Our Creator shaped the Earth\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 And by His Supreme Commands\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 He determines what He wishes\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Why fear losing along the way?\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Knowing your Father is with you\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Be not afraid of anyone\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Not even of yourself\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Few are capable of very much\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Except that it be stopped\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Have courage and be brave\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Your Father will answer your call\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 And His knowledge is complete\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Glory and destruction in His design\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Are both only 7 precise steps away\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Amazing God, Who Heals People!\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Righteous Creator, Who Sends Rain!\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Supporting Verses\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab \u8220"I have told you these things, so that in me you may have peace. In this world you will have trouble. But take heart! I have overcome the world.\u8221" - John 16:33\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab \u8220"Then Jesus said to him, \u8220"Get up! Pick up your mat and walk.\u8221" At once the man was cured; he picked up his mat and walked.\u8221" - John 5:8-9\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 File: app/(poems)/his-design/value-the-weight/page.mdx\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Value the Weight\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Life is full of fleeting distractions\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The Earth itself makes promises it cannot keep\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The surface reveals little of what is within\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 While the petty things demand much\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Remember that which feeds the soul\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Truly it is the Word of God\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Surely it is love and the next life\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 So do not let the attractive things persuade you\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Neither dishonor people for small wrongs\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 But appreciate the weighty matters\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 And celebrate that which is worthy\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 File: app/(poems)/salvation/be-generous/page.mdx\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Be Generous\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 What is life at all,\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 If you have nothing to remember?\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Why should a child have no where to turn,\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Crying out, \u8220"Father, help! God, save me!\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Words cannot describe the pain\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Even images cannot depict the horror\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 For suffering is a private experience\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Let those with food eat it\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 So that they may not be tired\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Make them not lazy or over restful,\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Give them empathy for hardship\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 There is pain in the work\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 There are struggles and costs\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 But be grateful amidst your pain\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 And deliver relief to the others\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Give your life by devoting it to giving back\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Lay it down by your work\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 And build God\u8217's Kingdom on Earth\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Taking part in the Salvation of Jesus\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Come to God with wisdom\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Approach Him humbly\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 He does not lead all people\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The one who gets excited by money\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Or the one full of dreams and fantasies\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 About riches or fame or Earthly success\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 He shows love and uplifts His Chosen\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Who heed guidance selflessly\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Who dream of giving back\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 And expect nothing in return\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Our Father will strengthen them,\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 He will help and deliver them!\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 People and angels have honored many gifts\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Some a fraction, some a tenth, others a third\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Some say to give what\u8217's left beyond needs\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Yet God does not ask any of these of you\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Almighty God, in all His Power, calls you out\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 He asks that you give all you have to the poor\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Do it all at once, and then follow Jesus\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Yes, be generous whenever you can\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 But don\u8217't be deceived by wealth and life\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Be not afraid at all\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 For not only will you survive your gift\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Even more, you shall truly find your own life\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Even when you doubt, Jesus shall catch you\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Truly, the one who gives all will see the Power of God\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 But what of the single parents,\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 What about the children?\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 What of those whose hearts are not ready?\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Certainly, Your Father will always accept your gift\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Yet begin work for His sake, and when you do,\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Do not turn back\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Praise God!\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 He doesn\u8217't want to place His sheep in danger\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 So do not let the old ways of travel be your means of travel\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 For some there was a donkey, for others a camel\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 For us there is both the vehicle and the internet\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Give your provision, your resources\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Give your time, your knowledge\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Be a knowledgeable servant\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Hide away from the public eye\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Let your giving be in secret\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 So God may reward you in Paradise\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 And your gift may be between you and Him\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Supporting Verses\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab \u8220"Jesus answered,\u160 ?\u8220"If you want to be perfect,\u160 ?go, sell your possessions and give to the poor,\u160 ?and you will have treasure in heaven.\u160 ?Then come, follow me.\u8221" - Matthew 19:21\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab \u8220"But Zacchaeus stood up and said to the Lord,\u160 ?\u8220"Look, Lord! Here and now I give half of my possessions to the poor, and if I have cheated anybody out of anything,\u160 ?I will pay back four times the amount.\u8221" Jesus said to him,\u160 ?\u8220"Today salvation has come to this house, because this man, too, is a son of Abraham.\u8221" - Luke 19:8-9\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab \u8220"But when you give to the needy, do not let your left hand know what your right hand is doing,\u160 ?so that your giving may be in secret. Then your Father, who sees what is done in secret, will reward you.\u8221" - Matthew 6:3-4\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab \u8220"Give to the one who asks you, and do not turn away from the one who wants to borrow from you.\u8221" - Matthew 5:42\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab \u8220"So when you give to the needy, do not announce it with trumpets, as the hypocrites do in the synagogues and on the streets, to be honored by others. Truly I tell you, they have received their reward in full.\u8221" - Matthew 6:2\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab \u8220"So do not worry, saying, \u8216'What shall we eat?\u8217' or \u8216'What shall we drink?\u8217' or \u8216'What shall we wear?\u8217' For the pagans run after all these things, and your heavenly Father knows that you need them.\u160 ?But seek first his kingdom\u160 ?and his righteousness, and all these things will be given to you as well.\u8221" - Matthew 6:31-33\par}
