{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Call to Him\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li720 \fi0 {\b Prayer of Virtue:} When I fight, help me to not fight When I am impatient, help me to be patient When I am proud, help me to be humble When I am wild, help me into self-control When I hold grudges, help me to release them When I am angry, help me to find inner peace When I deceive others, help me to purify myself Amen\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The People are blessed with power\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Power to speak inwardly and to be heard\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Our God listens to what is not spoken aloud\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 And He knows when you acknowledge Him in your heart\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 It is a power called prayer, it is one of His great joys\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Prayer should be honest and true\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 He desires not that you hide from Him\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Be genuine about your hardships\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Praying earnestly about your hopes and wishes\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Be loving, giving Him your praise and thanks\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Do not pray with many words\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 One can speak to Him in a moment\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Another may spend a while in stillness\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 He listens to your heart, He knows what is unsaid\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 There are many different ways to pray\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 But it is the genuine who Our Father always accepts\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Pray not for riches\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Pray not for selfish gain\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Our Father loves prayers to gain virtue\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 He answers prayers which help others\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The one who makes a prayer for the right things\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Only needs a dash of faith for it all to come true\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 One who calls out to the Creator longs for Him secretly\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 He hears their cry and shows them mercy\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Yet it is the loving time obeying His Gospel,\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 And the regular prayer which grows your relationship\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Our Father loves our dedicated time alone with Him\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Whether once, three, or five times a day\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Give Him time in prayer, in worship, or in study\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Indeed, it is not too much, it is due Him\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
