{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Follow Jesus\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Indeed, Our God had a Son who lived on Earth\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 He was selfless and full of love and peace\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Yet he lived a life of poverty and difficulty\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Yes, Our Father chose One to be called His Own\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 And the One chosen called us brothers and sisters\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 His name is Jesus Christ\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The Holy Lamb who was slain\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Jesus is the coming Lord over All Earth\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The compassionate Savior of mankind\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Created since before creation, the living Gospel\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 A truth which was true before time and now\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 He is the first messenger of the Gospel\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The One who healed the multitudes\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The only direct way to the Creator, Our Father\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 And the one called Life-Giving Messiah\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The Prophets labored hard in the fields\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 But Jesus brings life to the People\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Indeed, Jesus always brought life\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 From his earliest years as a young one\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 He astounded those who listened\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 And he amazed elders at his teaching\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 But Jesus power was not only in his teaching\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 For he had the Creator on his side\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 He confidently performed feats of healing\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 With authority he rid people of their sickness\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Before long, crowds began to follow him\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 But he said, the glory is God\u8217's, and it was\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Yet it was Jesus that God had confirmed\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 By giving him such power in the sight of others\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 In time, Jesus teachings were collected\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 They were shared with passion and devotion\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Now, these poems share his message once again\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Along with other teachings of science and wisdom\par}
