{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Have Forgiveness\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Our Creator sees what we are unaware of\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 He forgives and shows us mercy every day\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Yet He does not forgive the unforgiving people\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 So Jesus taught us to forgive with strength\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Pay close attention to yourself\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Resentment has been the captor of many\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Revenge and penalty a common pit\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Forgiveness is from the heart\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 It speaks not a word against anyone\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 It seeks out the best of memories\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Even when the pains are great\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 God desires that you forgive\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Even when you\u8217're too weak to keep forgiving\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 God wants you to pray for strength\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Yes, it is your constancy in forgiveness\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Which brings Our Father to approval\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Indeed, Our God loves to forgive those who forgive\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 He will not hold those forgiven to account\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Supporting Verses\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab \u8220"For if you forgive other people when they sin against you, your heavenly Father will also forgive you. But if you do not forgive others their sins, your Father will not forgive your sins.\u8221" - Matthew 6:14-15\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 File: app/(poems)/salvation/love-one-another/page.mdx\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Love One Another\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Jesus spoke God\u8217's Word\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 And he gave commands from God\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Yet only few commands were given\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 To love your God is the greatest commandment\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 One without wisdom can live by it\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Our God exalts love above all knowledge\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Indeed, love your Creator ahead of all things\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Truly He is your Father and looks after you\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 What can be more important than Him?\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 He\u8217's the Good One who is always there for you\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 And love those who cross your path\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Have compassion for their hardship\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Overlook their wrongs and help them\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 For love is the most pleasing to your Father\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Indeed, love is the most powerful force\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 It can drive people across the whole earth\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 And love can heal a person\u8217's inner self\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 So manifest love in its many forms\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 And you will be greater than a monk or priest\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Treat your opposers like friends\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Remind them their Creator loves them also\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Indeed, Our God is greater than wars and grudges\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 His Love is not hampered by our mutual grievances\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Relieve the load for another\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 And take on suffering as love\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Labor for their health\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Give them your time\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 And what you value\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This example Jesus set for us\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 By giving his life so we could have ours\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Pray for love in all your words\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Pray for love in all that you do\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Speak pleasantly unto others\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Speak the truth\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Be not two-faced\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Choose gentle words\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Search out the light in people\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Find the good in what they do\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Be empathetic out of your love\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Give thought to others feelings\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Consider their perspectives\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Show you feel what they feel\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Love may consist of doing good deeds\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Yet the deepest love is unconditional\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Those with God\u8217's Love in their hearts,\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Give love without it being earned\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Be not partial to anyone\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Give love to the unloved\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Give attention to the forgotten\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Forgive the pariah\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
