{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Don\u8217't Love Poison\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 How easy it is to honor an excellent person\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 But the mirror is full of disapproval\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Might you despise yourself for your life?\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Yet your Creator loves your soul more than body\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The body finds itself in decay\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Strength is given way, time is poured\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 A food unlike the fruits, a poisonous berry\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Patiently, you eat, slowly, it also eats\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Oneself is low but also high\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Indulging in the seductive taste\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Coming back to drink and to buy\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Gaining now, and losing later\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Returning again and again\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 To give your health, to pay the premium\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This is addiction, one of Satan\u8217's dreams\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 What is worth little shall cost you much\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 File: app/(poems)/substances-and-health/stay-healthy/page.mdx\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Stay Healthy\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Our Creator is the greatest scientist\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 He has knowledge of the smallest things\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 So be mindful of what is around you\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Also be mindful of your own body\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Indeed, be watchful over your whole health\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 And eat what is safe and nourishing\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Wouldn\u8217't it be heartbreaking not to care for yourself\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 And to find your body wasting away\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Awaiting a slow death, slow to appear?\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 But science drives machines\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 And machines in turn provide your harvest\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 So be conscious of science\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Humbly accepting the truth as it is\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 File: app/(poems)/substances-and-health/use-right/page.mdx\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Use Right\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Our Father is not pleased by drunkenness\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 He does not like outbursts or aggression\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Nor does He love sleeping all the time\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 One should walk and talk carefully\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Avoiding heavy drugs and overuse\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Such drugs are intended for doctors\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Others lose strength, but keep victims\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 One should choose what to take with patience,\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 And should remain in control of themselves\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 File: app/(poems)/suffering/be-not-weak/page.mdx\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Be Not Weak\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Our Father is the poor\u8217's advocate\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 He helps the helpless\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Without Him, tyrants would rage on\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The unheard would have no voice\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 When the quake is great\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 And the devastation moreso\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Strongmen are broke to pieces\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 And thoughts long forgotten\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Will return to nurture evils\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Without strength, who can overcome?\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Full of pride, who can please God?\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Indeed, He is near the weak and loves them\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Yet through prayer He will strengthen you\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 God Overcomes All,\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 God Bestows All Strength!\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 File: app/(poems)/suffering/beware-of-carnage/page.mdx\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Beware of Carnage\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 O, Father, help the stranded one\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Help those taken by calamity\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Hurricanes lay homes to ruin\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The wildfire leaves ash behind\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Indeed, the chronic pains are weighty\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Just as the horrors and their traumas\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Like the winds and rains raged inside\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Causing all sorts of inner loss\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The victim is left to rebuild\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Given only examples of evil\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Numb to all sorts of hurtful things\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The loving will understand\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 A victim\u8217's unrighteous ways\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Form no godly basis for judgement\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 File: app/(poems)/suffering/cry-no-more/page.mdx\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Cry No More\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Darkness always comes in time\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 We all grieve in time, for the Earth is no home\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Our past haunts us even today\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Hardships last far past their hope\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Is the Earth just crumbling rock?\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Is there no sense in what happens to us?\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Nay, God Directs All Things!\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 All The Sand and All The Snow!\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Might I fail in an endeavor\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 God prepares me for another\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Might I lose my shelter\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 God keeps for me a blanket\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Might I never find true love\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 God shows His Love instead\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Missing what you have lost\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Remembering what you never had\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Trials call for more than you have\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 What you have calls for more love\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 There is no strength or desire\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Your Father calls you away\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Away from the whole world\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Indeed, it is a futile place\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Few escape Earth\u8217's suffering\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Your Creator calls you to Him\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Where trials lose their power\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 And what you\u8217've had pales in comparison\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Unlike eternal life and His Love\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 For your God is a caring Creator\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 He is filled with sorrow at your suffering\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 So give to others and call upon Him\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 He is always near and complete in knowledge\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 File: app/(poems)/suffering/endure-affliction/page.mdx\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Endure Affliction\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 God\u8217's Children do like the Angels\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Greater in heart and in mind, full of love\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Attacks and traps do not distract them\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 They be kind, they wish blessings in return\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Long sentences doom not His faithful\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 They will pray for patience and strength\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Though they will become numb to their pain\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Without declining, but bearing good fruit\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Be not in despair at all\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Darkness doesn\u8217't teach\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 But its victims do learn\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Take heed of simple corrections\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 And do good amidst tribulations\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Even taking on pain all day and night\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Speak not empty words, but God\u8217's Word\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Your trial will test you in some way\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 So always return to His Will\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 God will send you relief\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 He will give it where you do not expect it\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 File: app/(poems)/suffering/escape-the-fire/page.mdx\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Escape the Fire\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The fire will boil your inner self\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Its caretakers will blame you\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 What a woeful home it is\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Might you learn despite this?\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Might you have reverence for your Creator\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 So your love could overflow,\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Even seeing the light in your captors?\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The fire will take everything\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 You will cry out and be abandoned\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Like a prisoner or slave\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 But can\u8217't God save you even now?\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 With faith, might you pray to Him,\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 And with heart, forgive again and again?\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Yes, He Determines All Things!\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Always, God is The Most Capable!\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Those dark times will trap you\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Escape is an invisible door for you\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Dark times bring us to survive\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 And survival is not progress\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Indeed, dark times beget dark times\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Its victim must search for a way\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Yet it will remain covered and out of reach\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Until one changes and does what God wills\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 God guides him to act righteously\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Knowing his life does not beget righteousness\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Let him give unto others heavenly times\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Let God be pleased and reward him plenty\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Seek not to send people into hard times\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 You seek a benefit\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 But incur the cost and its penalties\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Rather, be of the most helpful\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Pull a person out of his suffering now\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 And teach him his way out afterwards\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 File: app/(poems)/the-people/his-servants/page.mdx\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 His Servants\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Prophets have blessed knowledge upon us\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 They have given their lives for God\u8217's cause\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 They are beholden only to Our Lord, the One True God\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 They taught us of wisdom and events to come\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Among them are many, known and unknown\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Surely, they all labor hard for the Lord\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Yet they are only given knowledge by angels\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 None of them are like Our Savior, Jesus Christ\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Indeed, it was He who taught us the ways of Our Father\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 It was He who washed away the sins of many\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 And He who healed the disabled, the possessed, and even the dead\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 File: app/(poems)/the-people/one-book/page.mdx\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 One Book\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Among the greatest books of all time\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 You will find the Psalms of David\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Perched next to it are the Proverbs of Solomon\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Calling all who seek God and wisdom\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Yet only the Gospel is timeless\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The others are from angels or mere men\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 People may learn from many prophets\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 But only Jesus delivers the true Word of God\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Bring the Parables of Jesus close to you\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Plant them securely and do away with wordplay\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 For the light in His teaching is brighter than all the stars\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 And His love is greater than the breadth of the universe\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 File: app/(poems)/the-people/one-church/page.mdx\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 One Church\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 As believers we gather together\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Together we praise and worship our God in love\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 We share teaching and help each other grow in the Word\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 And we dedicate time to giving back to the poor\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Yet out of Churches may come difficulty and pressure\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Some invest in themselves more than they give back\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 And others involve themselves in government matters\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Why bring Caesar into a place of worship?\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Let your mind be your first Church\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Ask God to make it into a worthy dwelling\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 You needn\u8217't appear before Church people\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 No requirement has been made of you\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 File: app/(poems)/the-straight-path/act-honorably/page.mdx\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Act Honorably\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Our God delights in those who seek wisdom\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 He supports those who desire to be honorable\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 For Our God is on the side of the righteous\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Set an example for others that is safe\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 If they act like you, they should find goodness\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 So do what is honorable and repeatable\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Seek out what is good of those who succeed\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Be aware of the wisdom in their deeds\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Persevering in what is loving and forgiving\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Let your honor be a part of your character\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Have integrity and do what is right in private\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Understanding that good deeds are not for a show\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Much will tempt you towards sin and evil\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Saying, \u8220"Believe me, this is for your benefit\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Yet evil deeds carry no more weight for success\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Than the good deeds which are born of love\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 File: app/(poems)/the-straight-path/act-in-secret/page.mdx\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Act in Secret\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 We don\u8217't flaunt our belief\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 We don\u8217't wear our faith\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Indeed, we do not do good deeds to be seen\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Though we let our light shine before others\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 For Our Father loves to see a good example\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 And He rewards those who do not glorify themselves\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
