{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Be Humble\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Recall when Our Savior humbled himself\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 And showed his love and heart of forgiveness\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 By washing his disciple\u8217's feet by hand\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Who can turn away from all wealth,\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 And who can turn away from all power,\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 So that he could show his love to his people?\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 That is the love of Jesus Christ\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 That is the value of a humble heart\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 So take not the high spot in your affairs\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Rather, take the low spot without fear\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 For this reflects your heart to God\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 And do not walk about in an overbearing way\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Do not be pretentious or egotistical\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 But let yourself appear as less than others\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The humble cannot possibly stand before God\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 For they consider themselves unworthy and incapable\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Yet God is completely capable and always wins\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Supporting Verses\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab \u8220"But when you are invited, take the lowest place, so that when your host comes, he will say to you, \u8216'Friend, move up to a better place.\u8217' Then you will be honored in the presence of all the other guests. For all those who exalt themselves will be humbled, and those who humble themselves will be exalted.\u8221"\u8221" - Luke 14:10-11\par}
