{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Walk Straight\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Hypocrites expect from others correct behavior\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 But they do not practice it themselves\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 They condemn others for evil deeds\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 But run when they are condemned likewise\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 They provide special allowances for some\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 While others worthy of those privileges are denied\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The hypocrites say, \u8220"Condemn him\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 But they lack foresight, and thereby condemn themselves\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Those who are straight in their hearts and minds\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 They have no inner conflict\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 And they repent for their failings\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Those who please God will tolerate what they dislike\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 And they will practice what they believe in\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Our God protects His loyal believers\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 He lets nothing fall except what He allows\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 He holds up the straight and honest\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 He shelters them from calamity\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 And heals their inner diseases\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Supporting Verses\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab \u8220"How can you say to your brother, \u8216'Let me take the speck out of your eye,\u8217' when all the time there is a plank in your own eye?\u160 ?You hypocrite, first take the plank out of your own eye, and then you will see clearly to remove the speck from your brother\u8217's eye.\u8221" - Matthew 7:4-5\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 File: app/(poems)/the-straight-path/work-in-peace/page.mdx\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Work in Peace\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Life is full of work\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 For by your contribution\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 You shall earn a due reward\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Thereby feeding yourself and your children\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 So seek wisdom in all your work\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Do not neglect your contribution\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Do not fall for deceitful shortcuts\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Work with prudence, avoiding haste\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Work with much patience\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Years may pass before you are finished\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Be a worthy partner and friend\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Respect those you work with\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Even assure your continued strength\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Take time to relax and rejuvenate\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Knowing that laziness leads to poverty\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 And poverty does not help the poor\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 File: app/(poems)/the-way/blessed-costs/page.mdx\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Blessed Costs\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 If you really cared for the poor, you would work for their sake\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 If you really cared for the poor, you would take on their hardships\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 If you really cared for the poor, you would be friends with them\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Our Father blesses the one who blesses others\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 He equips him and builds him up and gives him strength\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Our Father raises up His Children and separates the bad from the good\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 He causes one to lose part of himself so that he might grow\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Doing good is for the long-term investor\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 For in all good things, there is both a cost and a reward\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Take up the burden of others, take up the mission of God\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 For in all great blessings, one shall incur the cost of his blessing\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 So when you turn your cheek, you shall incur the sting\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 And when you go the extra mile, you shall incur the expense\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 When you care for the sick, your wealth shall decrease\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Take up the burden of others, take up the mission of God\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 File: app/(poems)/the-way/do-good/page.mdx\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Do Good\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Imagine what people have done to succeed\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Think of the lengths they traverse to attain wealth\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 People have strained themselves for Earthly treasures\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Knowing these treasures disappear when death comes\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 But the jewels which are eternal never disappear\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 And doing good deeds is possible even for the poorest\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 So traverse those same lengths to attain goodness\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 And you will find yourself rich in Heaven\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Shall you seek out good word?\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Or do you seek out the words of an orator\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Shall you put your thoughts on goodness?\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Or do you think only of what is advantageous\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Shall you put work into good deeds?\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Or do you focus solely on your goals\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Seek out what is good, and have faith in God\u8217's cause\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Then He will grant you all that is needed\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Supporting Verses\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab \u8220"No one can serve two masters. Either you will hate the one and love the other, or you will be devoted to the one and despise the other. You cannot serve both God and money.\u8221" - Luke 16:13\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab \u8220"Receive my instruction instead of silver, and knowledge rather than pure gold. For wisdom is more precious than rubies, and nothing you desire compares with her.\u8221" - Proverbs 8:10-11\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 File: app/(poems)/the-way/fear-him/page.mdx\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Fear Him\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Yet remain on your guard\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Make sure you are self-aware\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 For Our God is always watching\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 And He is always the winner\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Be ready, the rich people\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 And the evil ones alike\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 There is a penalty prepared\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 And it is truly unbearable\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Unlike the Heavenly Afterlife of Paradise\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 It is full of pain and anguish\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 So repent for your sins\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Forgive and give your money\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Otherwise you may leave Earth\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Only to meet a blazing fire\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Supporting Verses\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab \u8220"Do not be afraid of those who kill the body but cannot kill the soul. Rather, be afraid of the One who can destroy both soul and body in hell.\u8221" - Matthew 10:28\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 File: app/(poems)/the-way/go-his-way/page.mdx\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Go His Way\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Our God created the Heavens and the Earth\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 He determined what is good and called it His own\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 While Satan did everything else and it was all evil\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Wisdom and righteousness are to be sought after\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Folly and wickedness are Satan\u8217's joys and they are sin\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 God\u8217's Children are on the side of the light\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Their enemies are completely wayward\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The pain of trials strengthen a person\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 But woe unto the one who delivers trials\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 For the relief of gifts rescue a lost one\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 And it is the generous who are destined for peace\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 File: app/(poems)/the-way/hope-for-a-new-life/page.mdx\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Hope for a New Life\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Life is full of suffering and none is spared\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The Earth barely sustains its people\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 For man needs not grain, but the Love of God\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Yet hope remains for those in despair\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 For the Love of God fuels an endless energy\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Capable of sustaining countless lives\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 So have high hopes for a Heavenly Paradise\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Our Father loves us enough for home\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Do not give Hell too much attention\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Knowing God is not full of animosity\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 File: app/(poems)/the-way/mind-the-times/page.mdx\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Mind the Times\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Rituals bring a people closer together\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 As habits they build solidarity\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Exalted falsely as a means of salvation\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 They carry burdens and relieve them also\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 When something is done regularly for God\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 It only matters when done with heart\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 One who is genuine towards God pleases Him\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 But one who obeys reluctantly should pray\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The repentant wash before prayer\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 But the water does not save\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The modest cover their heads\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 But the clothing does not save\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Your Creator does not require these rituals\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 He desires the virtues in their hearts\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 So let your faith nurture itself within you\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Ask Your Father to lead you unto the honorable\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Indeed, if you are blessed with knowledge\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 You will be mindful of the times\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Honor the people who rest routinely\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Every Sunday on the Sabbath Day\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The people do not work for the sake of God\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Unless someone is in need of help\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 And honor those who watch the Moon\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 In Ramadan is one month of fasting\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Except in the early mornings\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 And in the late evenings\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Our Father has set out His vision\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 In the Age to Come with peace on Earth\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 All the people will obey the One True God\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 And believe in the one Messiah, Jesus Christ\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Worship and Love your Creator!\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 He gives Strength to the Weak!\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Supporting Verses\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab \u8220"\u8220"As the new heavens and the new earth that I make will endure before me,\u8221" declares the Lord, \u8220"so will your name and descendants endure. From one New Moon to another and from one Sabbath to another, all mankind will come and bow down before me,\u8221" says the Lord.\u8221" - Isaiah 66:22-23\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab \u8220"Nothing outside a person can defile them by going into them. Rather, it is what comes out of a person that defiles them.\u8221" - Mark 7:15\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab \u8220"Then Jesus asked them, \u8220"Which is lawful on the Sabbath: to do good or to do evil, to save life or to kill?\u8221" But they remained silent.\u8221" - Mark 3:4\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 File: app/(poems)/the-way/seek-not-earth/page.mdx\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Seek Not Earth\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 People seek after life from the Earth\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The lifeless Earth beneath their feet\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The perfume is for only a short time\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 But your love should never decay\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The fire lasts only a few hours\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 But God\u8217's Love shall never fade\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Our Father watches always\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Not a thought escapes His Sight\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 His Majesty is met with you\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Though billions roam the Earth\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 He cares for each morning\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 And if you shall manifest His Ways\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Your mornings shall be lovely indeed\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Supporting Verses\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab \u8220"Whoever loves his life will lose it, but whoever hates his life in this world will keep it for eternal life.\u8221" - John 12:25\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab \u8220"Do not store up for yourselves treasures on earth, where moth and rust destroy, and where thieves break in and steal. But store up for yourselves treasures in heaven, where moth and rust do not destroy, and where thieves do not break in and steal.\u8221" - Matthew 6:19-20\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 File: app/(poems)/the-way/spread-the-word/page.mdx\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Spread the Word\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Never leave the lost behind\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 For darkness is waiting to overtake them\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Your Father loves the little birds\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 He even gives life to the ants and bees\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Consider how much He loves those lost\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Truly, He would give away all His possessions\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 To fill their hearts with faith\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Our Father blesses the one who saves others\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The one who searches and does not stop\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Has the Love of God in his heart\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Our hearts ache over those lost and alone\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Their souls are worth more than perfection\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 So be not above anyone\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Do not fight with the unbelievers\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Rather, be understanding, and accept them!\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Befriend them!\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Yes, Your Father asks that you share the Gospel\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Yet in these poems there is power,\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Power to echo Jesus and strengthen the people!\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 So pass these poems along to your children\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Bringing God\u8217's glory to fill your house\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Supporting Verses\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab \u8220"I tell you that in the same way there will be more rejoicing in heaven over one sinner who repents than over ninety-nine righteous persons who do not need to repent.\u8221"- Luke 15:7\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab \u8220"In the same way, I tell you, there is rejoicing in the presence of the angels of God over one sinner who repents.\u8221" - Luke 15:10\par}
